# BROWSER-notifications.md - LinkedIn Notification, Reply & Connection Patterns

## SS 1. Extract Notifications

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    var notifications = document.querySelectorAll('[data-finite-scroll-hotkey-item]');
    return Array.from(notifications).slice(0, 15).map(function(notif) {
      var card = notif.querySelector('.nt-card');
      var text = notif.innerText;
      var links = Array.from(notif.querySelectorAll('a'));
      var isReply = text.includes('commented on') || text.includes('replied to') || text.includes('mentioned you in a comment');
      var isLike = text.includes('reacted to') || text.includes('liked');
      var profileLink = links.find(function(a) { return a.href.includes('/in/'); });
      var activityLink = links.find(function(a) { return a.href.includes('/feed/update/') || a.href.includes('/activity/'); });
      var username = profileLink ? (profileLink.href.match(/\/in\/([^/?]+)/) || [])[1] : null;
      // Keep full URL for navigation (has commentUrn for thread targeting) but store base URL for tracking
      var fullUrl = activityLink ? activityLink.href : null;
      var baseUrl = fullUrl ? fullUrl.split('?')[0] : null;
      return {
        type: isReply ? 'reply' : (isLike ? 'like' : 'other'),
        username: username,
        postUrl: fullUrl,
        baseUrl: baseUrl,
        preview: text.slice(0, 200),
        unread: card ? card.classList.contains('nt-card--unread') : false
      };
    }).filter(function(n) { return n.type === 'reply' && n.postUrl && n.username; });
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

## SS 5. Reply to Comment (Post Detail Page)

Post pages have multiple TipTap editors. For notification replies, MUST click Reply on the target comment first to open the correct threaded editor.

### Step 0: Click Reply on the target comment (MANDATORY for notification replies)

🚨 **Do NOT add a page-level `alreadyReplied` check** (looking for our profile link on page) — our ORIGINAL comment is always present on notification pages, causing false positives. The tracking file grep (§ 3 step 4) is the ONLY reliable dedup for notifications.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    // Find the comment that replied to us — must START with author name AND contain the snippet
    var comments = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[class*="comment"]'));
    var targetComment = comments.find(c => c.innerText.trim().startsWith('${notificationAuthor}') && c.innerText.includes('${notificationPreviewSnippet}'));
    if (!targetComment) {
      // Fallback: starts with author name + @mentions us
      targetComment = comments.find(c => c.innerText.trim().startsWith('${notificationAuthor}') && c.innerText.includes('{{name}}'));
    }
    if (!targetComment) return { error: 'target comment not found', commentCount: comments.length };
    // Click its Reply button
    var btns = Array.from(targetComment.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var replyBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Reply');
    if (!replyBtn) return { error: 'no Reply button on target comment' };
    replyBtn.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
    // Check editor opened INSIDE this comment (NOT globally — other threads have editors too)
    var editorInside = targetComment.querySelector('[contenteditable="true"][role="textbox"]');
    return { clicked: true, editorOpen: !!editorInside };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

If `editorOpen: false` → retry once. Still fails → skip, log error.

### Step 1: Type text in the THREADED reply editor (found by @mention)

🚨 **LinkedIn auto-inserts `@AuthorName` when Reply is clicked.** Find the editor containing this @mention — that's the correct threaded editor. Do NOT use `editors[last]` globally — it types into the wrong thread.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    // Find the editor that has the auto-inserted @mention (correct threaded editor)
    var editors = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[contenteditable="true"][role="textbox"]'));
    var replyBox = editors.find(e => e.textContent.includes('${notificationAuthor}'));
    if (!replyBox) return { success: false, reason: 'no-editor-with-mention' };
    replyBox.focus();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300));
    var text = "${replyText.replace(/"/g, '\\"').replace(/\n/g, '\\n')}";
    document.execCommand('insertText', false, text);
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
    return { success: true, typed: text.slice(0, 50) };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

### Step 2: Submit + verify (ONE async evaluate)
```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    // Find submit: feed uses data-view-name, post pages use class
    var btn = document.querySelector('button[data-view-name="comment-post"]');
    if (!btn) btn = document.querySelector('button.comments-comment-box__submit-button--cr');
    if (!btn) {
      var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
      btn = btns.find(b => (b.innerText.trim() === 'Reply' || b.innerText.trim() === 'Comment') && b.getBoundingClientRect().width > 0 && b.getAttribute('data-view-name') !== 'feed-comment-button');
    }
    if (!btn) return { success: false, reason: 'no-submit-button' };
    if (btn.disabled) return { success: false, reason: 'button-disabled' };
    btn.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    var snippet = "${expectedSnippet.replace(/"/g, '\\"')}";
    var posted = document.body.innerText.includes(snippet);
    return { submitted: true, posted: posted };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

If NOT posted: retry ONCE (will wait another 3s). Still fails → do NOT log, retry next heartbeat.

### When to use SS 5 vs top-level comment:
- **Notification replies** (§ 3 in HEARTBEAT.md): ALWAYS use Step 0 first → Step 1 → Step 2 (threaded reply)
- **Proactive comments** (§ 4 browse_and_engage): Use BROWSER-engage.md SS 4 (TipTap editor, no Step 0)

## SS 7. Send Connection Request (with personalized note)

🚨 **Verified 2026-03-26:** On many profiles the "Connect" button is hidden inside the "More" dropdown menu (not a direct action button). The connection flow opens an "Add a note to your invitation?" dialog.

🚨 **ALWAYS add a personalized note.** Notes significantly increase acceptance rates.

### Flow: Navigate to profile → Safety check → Navigate to custom-invite URL → Add note → Send

### Step 1: Safety checks (on profile page, after navigate + 3s wait)

🚨 **Detection uses buttons, NOT body text** — `bodyText.includes('Pending')` false-positives on navbar/notification text.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    var vanity = window.location.pathname.replace('/in/', '').replace(/\\/$/, '');
    // Profile action detection: "Follow" button with aria-label="Follow {Name}" = NOT connected
    // "Message" without "Follow" = already 1st-degree connected
    // "Pending" = connection request already sent
    var els = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button, a')).filter(e => e.offsetParent !== null && e.getBoundingClientRect().y < 600);
    var hasFollow = els.some(e => (e.getAttribute('aria-label') || '').startsWith('Follow ' + vanity.replace(/-/g, ' ').split(' ')[0]));
    if (!hasFollow) hasFollow = els.some(e => e.innerText.trim() === 'Follow' && (e.getAttribute('aria-label') || '').startsWith('Follow'));
    var hasPending = els.some(e => e.innerText.trim() === 'Pending');
    // 1st-degree: has Message but NO Follow button for this person
    if (!hasFollow && !hasPending) return { canConnect: false, skipReason: 'already-connected', vanityName: vanity };
    if (hasPending) return { canConnect: false, skipReason: 'already-pending', vanityName: vanity };
    // Extract headline for recruiter check
    var bodyText = document.body.innerText.slice(0, 1500);
    var lines = bodyText.split('\\n');
    var headline = '';
    for (var i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
      if (lines[i].trim() === 'Follow' || lines[i].trim() === 'More') {
        for (var j = i - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
          if (lines[j].trim().length > 0) { headline = lines[j].trim(); break; }
        }
        break;
      }
    }
    var recruiterKeywords = ['Recruiter', 'Recruiting', 'Talent Acquisition', 'Hiring Manager', 'HR', 'Headhunter'];
    for (var k = 0; k < recruiterKeywords.length; k++) {
      if (headline.includes(recruiterKeywords[k])) return { canConnect: false, headline: headline.slice(0, 150), skipReason: 'recruiter-headline', vanityName: vanity };
    }
    return { canConnect: true, headline: headline.slice(0, 150), vanityName: vanity };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

If `canConnect: false` → log `Type=Connection Skipped, Reason={skipReason}`, continue.

### Step 2: Navigate to custom-invite URL (opens Add Note dialog)

```
browser.navigate("https://www.linkedin.com/preload/custom-invite/?vanityName={vanityName}")
```

Wait 3s. Page shows "Add a note to your invitation?" with "Add a note" and "Send without a note" buttons.

### Step 3: Click "Add a note", type note, click Send

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    // Click "Add a note" button
    var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var addNoteBtn = btns.find(function(b) { return b.innerText.trim() === 'Add a note' && b.offsetParent !== null; });
    if (!addNoteBtn) return { sent: false, error: 'no Add a note button' };
    addNoteBtn.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500));
    // Find textarea and type note
    var textarea = document.querySelector('textarea#custom-message');
    if (!textarea) return { sent: false, error: 'no note textarea' };
    var note = ${JSON.stringify(connectionNote)};
    var nativeInputValueSetter = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(window.HTMLTextAreaElement.prototype, 'value').set;
    nativeInputValueSetter.call(textarea, note);
    textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
    textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    // Click Send
    btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var sendBtn = btns.find(function(b) { return b.innerText.trim() === 'Send' && b.offsetParent !== null; });
    if (!sendBtn) return { sent: false, typed: true, error: 'no Send button' };
    sendBtn.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
    return { sent: true };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

### Step 4: Verify (navigate back to profile)

Navigate back to profile URL, wait 3s, check for "Pending" in page text.

### Connection Note Rules

- Max 300 characters
- Personalize: reference their headline, role, or a post they wrote
- Keep casual, genuine — not salesy
- Template: "hey {firstName}, {specific thing you noticed about them}. {brief connection to your work}. would be great to connect"
- Examples:
  - "hey Daniel, loved your take on product execution at scale. would be great to connect and exchange notes on PM leadership"
  - "hey Sarah, your post about AI in product management resonated. been running 10+ AI agents as part of my PM workflow and would love to exchange notes"

- If `sent: true` → log `Type=Connection Request`, update `weekly.connection_requests`
- If `sent: false` → log `Type=Connection Skipped, Reason={error}`, continue

Navigate back to notifications after success.
